# ── Public repo policy ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Only the frontend source is published. The backend is distributed as a
# prebuilt binary via GitHub Releases, so its source, build tooling, and
# full-stack/internal files are kept out of the repository.
/backend/
/release/
/build_release.bat
# note: release_files/ (run.bat, README.txt for end users) IS published —
# the Release workflow packages them into the distributed archive.
/run.bat
/docker-compose.yml
/Makefile
/.env.example
/CLAUDE.md
/document_translation_service_development_spec.md
# Published in this repo: frontend/, docs/, README.md, LICENSE,
# THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.md
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

